  <section id="tribute-info">
    <h3 id="headline">A Brief Timeline of  Ross Perot .H </h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>1930</strong> - Ross Perot .H Born in Texarkana, Texas</li>
      <li>
        <strong>1947</strong> - He initially went to the Patty Hill private school and graduated from the Texas High School in Texarkana. He was part of the "Boys Scouts of America" and later became a part of the "U.S Naval Academy"
      </li><li>
        <strong>1956</strong> - He got married to Magrot Birmingham, who was from Greensburg, Pennsylania. The couple had five Children together, namely Ross Jr., Nancy, Suzanne, Carolyn, and Katherine. 
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>1957</strong> - He resigned from the Navy having reached the position of battalion commander. 
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>1962</strong> - He established and founded the Electronic Data Systems in Dallas, Texas and went through an initial struggle period, after which the company began receiving Contracts.
      </li><li>
        <strong>1984</strong> - The S. Roger Horchow Award for "Greatest Public Service by a Private Citizen" was bestowed upon him 
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>1988</strong> - He became the founder of the "Perot Systems Corporation, Inc.", the company was later acquired by "DELL, Inc."
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>1991</strong> He re-entered the presidential race after he had earlier quit following a controversy about his daughter and an apparent threat by the Republican government to leak compromising photos of his daughter.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>1992</strong> - He lost the presidential elections but polled 18.9% of the popular vote. with this, he became the most successful third party presidential candidate in terms of the popular vote since Theodore Roosevelt in the 1912 election.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2009</strong> - He was awarded the Honorary Green Beret at the John F. Kennedy Special Warfare Center, located at Fort Bragg, North Carolina.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2009</strong> - He received the Sylvanus Thayer Award, which was conferred upon him by the U.S Military Academy at West point.
      </li>
      <li><strong>2019</strong> - Ross Perot died in Dallas, Texas after being diagonised with leukaemia earlier in the year. </li>
    </ul>
    
